text.tspan: FRUSTRATIONS
He finds it difficult to keep track of the various medicines that
all the people have to take daily.
It is difficult for him to remember the room number as well as
the name of the person living there.
Cannot immediately attend emergency calls since he has to
first look up the register to find the room number, also he
does not have any idea of the emergency until he reaches
there.
GOALS
Support his family.
Immediately assist elderly people
whenever required.
Remind the people at the old age home
to take their medicines on time and
regularly monitor their health.
Inform doctors or family members of the
elderly people about their current health
status
ABOUT
Rajaram Soni is a poor person who used to work as a caretaker
at old age homes. He has been assisting elderly people in their
daily chores since years. He dropped out of school after
completing his SSC (10th standard) and started working
immediately. He uses a smartphone and is well versed with
different technology. He finds it difficult to have conversations
in English. However, he can read and write in English at a
moderate level.
LITERATE
HARD-WORKING
POOR
Rajaram Soni, 40
USER PERSONA
OF CARETAKER
